                                                    </p>
                                                    <ol class="how-steps mx-auto text-start">
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>Enter your domain and email address</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">We’ll use these to generate a certificate request.</span>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>Get a verification token</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">We’ll contact the certificate authority (<span class="domain-vendor">Let’s Encrypt</span>) and get a special token that proves you own the domain.</span>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>Add a <span class="domain-txt">TXT</span> record to your DNS</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">
                                                                Log into your provider (like <span class="domain-vendor">Cloudflare</span> or <span class="domain-vendor">Namecheap</span>), go to DNS settings, and create:<br>
                                                                <span class="how-substep">• <b>Name (host):</b> <span class="domain-example">_acme-challenge.yourdomain.com</span></span><br>
                                                                <span class="how-substep">• <b>Value:</b> the token we give you — and <b>yes, include the quotes</b> (<span class="domain-example">"your-token-here"</span>)!</span>
                                                                <br>
                                                                <span class="how-api-tip">(If you’re using Auto Add via API, we’ll handle this for you.)</span>
                                                            </span>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>Wait for DNS to propagate</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">Can take a few seconds to a few minutes. Chill, stretch, vibe. </span>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>We verify</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">Once DNS is updated, we’ll check if the <span class="domain-txt">TXT</span> record is correct. If it is — <span class="domain-success">boom!</span> You’re verified.</span>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <b>Get your SSL certificate</b>
                                                            <span class="how-detail">If all’s good, we’ll fetch your certificate files (<span class="domain-txt">.crt</span> &amp; <span class="domain-txt">.key</span> or <span class="domain-txt">.pem</span> ). You’re ready for HTTPS life!</span>
                                                        </li>
                                                    </ol>
                                                    <div class="mt-3">
                                                        <span class="how-tip">You don’t need to be a wizard  — just follow the steps, copy the token right, and <b>don’t forget those quotes</b>!</span>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
